# Naming Rules

## Files

| Kind                              | Convention            | Example                   |
|-----------------------------------|-----------------------|---------------------------|
| React components                  | `PascalCase.tsx`      | `ImageCard.tsx`           |
| Route segments (Next.js folders)  | `kebab-case`          | `app/admin/upload/`       |
| Hooks                             | `use*.ts`             | `useDebouncedSearch.ts`   |
| Services / repos / utils          | `camelCase.ts`        | `imageService.ts`         |
| Test files                        | `*.test.ts(x)`        | `imageService.test.ts`    |
| Type-only files                   | `*.types.ts`          | `image.types.ts`          |

Names must describe responsibility. Banned: `utils.ts`, `helpers.ts`, `common.ts`, `temp.ts`, `index.ts` *as the only file in a folder* (use a named file).

## Functions and methods

- `camelCase`, start with an action verb.
- Boolean accessors start with `is`/`has`/`can`/`should`.

```ts
// GOOD
fetchPublishedImages(); validateUploadPayload(); isFeatured(image);

// BAD
process(); handle(); doTask(); run(); execute();
```

## Variables

- `camelCase`, descriptive, full words.
- Single letters only as loop counters (`i`, `j`) or canonical math (`x`, `y`).
- Banned: `data`, `temp`, `obj`, `val`, `info`, `result` (too vague).

```ts
const meetingStartTime = ...;       // GOOD
const retryAttemptCount = ...;      // GOOD
const data = ...;                   // BAD
```

## Classes, types, interfaces, enums

- `PascalCase`. No `I` prefix on interfaces.
- Names express the responsibility, not the layer.

```ts
class ImageService {}             // GOOD
interface UploadPayload {}        // GOOD
class Manager {}                  // BAD
class IImageService {}            // BAD — no `I` prefix
```

## Constants

- `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` for module-level immutable values.
- Group related constants in `lib/constants/*.ts`, never inline magic values.
